      "content": "That's an interesting distinction. You mentioned that Defendant B's environment would be used as an aggravating factor. Could you expand on that? Specifically, why would his background be considered an \"aggravating factor\" in a legal sense rather than a mitigating one, since those circumstances are often out of his control?",
